TITLE: Integrating Custom Rsdoctor Version in Rspeedy Configuration
DESCRIPTION: TypeScript configuration for using a custom Rsdoctor version in an Rspeedy project. This snippet shows how to import and add the RsdoctorRspackPlugin to the Rspack configuration, with a note on production usage and required support for banner configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lynx-family/lynx-stack/blob/main/website/docs/en/guide/use-rsdoctor.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { RsdoctorRspackPlugin } from '@rsdoctor/rspack-plugin';

export default {
  tools: {
    rspack(config, { appendPlugins }) {
      if (process.env.RSDOCTOR === 'true') {
        appendPlugins(
          new RsdoctorRspackPlugin({
            // plugin options
            supports: { banner: true },
          }),
        );
      }
    },
  },
};
