TITLE: Extending Asset Types in Lynx Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to extend asset types by modifying the Rspack configuration to handle additional file types, such as PDFs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lynx-family/lynx-stack/blob/main/website/docs/en/guide/assets.md#2025-04-17_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import { defineConfig } from '@lynx-js/rspeedy';

export default defineConfig({
  tools: {
    rspack(config, { addRules }) {
      addRules([
        {
          test: /\.pdf$/,
          // converts asset to a separate file and exports the URL address.
          type: 'asset/resource',
        },
      ]);
      return config;
    },
  },
});
```

