TITLE: Defining WebSocket Event Interface and EventMap in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the Event interface and EventMap type for WebSocket events. It includes types for message, open, close, and error events, each with specific properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lynx-family/lynx-stack/blob/main/packages/rspeedy/websocket/etc/websocket.api.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
interface Event_2<T extends string> {
    // @internal (undocumented)
    target: WebSocketImpl;
    type: T;
}
export { Event_2 as Event }

export type EventMap = {
    message: Event_2<'message'> & {
        readonly data: string;
    };
    open: Event_2<'open'>;
    close: Event_2<'close'> & {
        readonly code: number;
        readonly reason: string;
    };
    error: Event_2<'error'> & {
        readonly message: string;
    };
};
```

