TITLE: Implementing Gesture Handling in Lynx Apps with React
DESCRIPTION: Example of using the gesture handler capabilities built on top of the Main Thread Script. This code demonstrates how to use the PanGesture with event handlers for begin, update, and end events, along with a state manager.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lynx-family/lynx-stack/blob/main/packages/react/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-17_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { useGesture, PanGesture } from '@lynx-js/gesture-runtime';

function App() {
  const pan = useGesture(PanGesture);

  pan
    .onBegin((event, stateManager) => {
      'main thread';
      // some logic
    })
    .onUpdate((event, stateManager) => {
      'main thread';
      // some logic
    })
    .onEnd((event, stateManager) => {
      'main thread';
      // some logic
    });

  return <view main-thread:gesture={pan}></view>;
}
```

