TITLE: Setting up NativeModulesMap with Blob URLs in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example code showing how to create a nativeModulesMap for a lynx-view element using URL.createObjectURL with a Blob. The module implementation demonstrates how to create a custom module with getColor functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/lynx-family/lynx-stack/blob/main/packages/web-platform/web-constants/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const nativeModulesMap = {
  CustomModule: URL.createObjectURL(
    new Blob(
      [
        `export default function(NativeModules, NativeModulesCall) {
    return {
      async getColor(data, callback) {
        const color = await NativeModulesCall('getColor', data);
        callback(color);
      },
    }
  };`,
      ],
      { type: 'text/javascript' },
    ),
  ),
};
lynxView.nativeModulesMap = nativeModulesMap;
```

